Target: OntoLab is an ontology developed for expressing facilities in a research lab.

Comment: Facility that provides controlled conditions in which scientific or technological research, experiments, and measurement may be performed. [https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q483242]
Label: Laboratory

Comment: Equipment used for laboratory experiments. [https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q834028]
Label: Laboratory equipment

Comment: Equipment used for laboratory safety.
Label: Safety equipment

Comment: Specifications that are used to set the operating conditions of laboratory equipment.
Label: Equipment settings

Comment: Each parameter setting refers to one specific setting of the laboratory equipment.
Label: Parameter setting

Comment: Setting that specifies the temperature.
Label: Temperature setting

Comment: Setting that specifies the duration.
Label: Duration setting

Comment: Setting that specifies the flow rate.
Label: Flow rate setting

Comment: Setting that specifies the volume.

Comment: A device that measures certain property of a sample and collects data of it.

Comment: A device that measures weight by using a calibrated counterweight
Label: Scale

Comment: A device that measures weight by measuring the force applied on a surface

Comment: A balance designed for very small masses; in the submiligram range.

Comment: A balance for small massses.Less accurate than an analytical balance.

Comment: A device that measures the smoke point temperature of a sample.
Label: Smoke-point lamp

Comment: A device that measures the particel size of a suspension.
Label: Grindometer

Comment: A device for analysing the composition of a gas sample or surrounding atmosphere.

Comment: A device for analysing the composition of a gas by running it through a separate medium.
Label: Gas chromatograph

Label: Galvanostat

Comment: A device for measuring energy going in or out of a system.
Label: Calorimeter

Comment: A device for analysing chemisorbed species on a surface.
Label: Chemisorption analyser

Comment: A device for measuring the amount of matter transformed during electrolysis reaction through measuring electricity consumed or produced.
Label: Coulometer

Comment: A device for measuring the amount of energy required to increase a sample's temperature by a certain amount.
Label: Differential scanning calorimeter

Comment: A devie for measuring the acidity of a solution
Label: pH meter

Comment: A spectrometer is any instrument used to probe a property of light as a function of its portion of the electromagnetic spectrum, typically its wavelength, frequency, or energy. ... Technically, a spectrometer can function over any range of light, but most operate in a particular region of the electromagnetic spectrum.
Label: Spectrometer

Comment: An infrared spectrophotometer is an analytical instrument used to identify materials including organic polymers.
Label: Infrared spectrum spectrometer

Comment: Mass spectrometry (MS) is an analytical technique that is used to measure the mass-to-charge ratio of ions. The results are typically presented as a mass spectrum, a plot of intensity as a function of the mass-to-charge ratio. Mass spectrometry is used in many different fields and is applied to pure samples as well as complex mixtures.
Label: Mass spectrometer

Comment: UV-Vis spectroscopy is an analytical technique that measures the amount of discrete wavelengths of UV or visible light that are absorbed by or transmitted through a sample in comparison to a reference or blank sample
Label: Ultraviolet-visible spectrum spectrometer

Comment: A spectrometer that uses changes in an x-ray energy to determine the content of the sample.
Label: X-ray spectrometer

Comment: A camera to capture specific electromagnetic wave for spectroscopy.
Label: Spectroscopy camera

Comment: A microscope is a laboratory instrument used to examine objects that are too small to be seen by the naked eye.
Label: Microscope

Comment: A device to analyse the component of a solution.
Label: High-performance liquid chromatography

Comment: A device that can act/ is composed of both a potentiostat and a galvanostat.

Label: Themo gravimetric analyser - Differential scanning calorimetry system
